    "body": "This is an updated version of #34793 after stickies-v [pointed out that the approach there was broken](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/34793#discussion_r2916369196).\r\n\r\nsync.h is low-level and should not require any other subsystems.\r\n\r\nMove the lone remaining logging call to the .cpp. Any cost incurred by an additional function call should be trivial compared to the logging itself.\r\n\r\nstickies-v suggested modernizing the c strings to `std::string_view`s, but I think that's best left as a follow-up, as all of the debugging functions should get the same treatment.",
